too closely to one of the sheep.

890
00:54:53,590 --> 00:54:54,499
You know what I mean?

891
00:54:56,250 --> 00:54:56,756
No.

892
00:54:58,150 --> 00:54:58,691
Look.

893
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:03,137
My dad did some stupid things, and
he got himself thrown out of the church.

894
00:55:03,300 --> 00:55:05,116
So we moved into
my grandma's house,

895
00:55:05,140 --> 00:55:07,877
and he started preaching
downtown to a bunch of crackheads.

896
00:55:08,310 --> 00:55:09,909
And my mom split and ran.

897
00:55:10,130 --> 00:55:11,039
Left us both.

898
00:55:13,190 --> 00:55:14,030
I'm sorry.

899
00:55:14,740 --> 00:55:15,465
Whatever.

900
00:55:16,925 --> 00:55:19,532
At least, I get a stupid Christmas
card from Belgium over here.

901
00:55:23,800 --> 00:55:24,433
What?

902
00:55:26,220 --> 00:55:27,600
You remind me of her.

903
00:55:27,780 --> 00:55:29,126
- Who?
- Montine.

904
00:55:29,780 --> 00:55:31,034
Oh gross!

905
00:55:31,230 --> 00:55:32,461
That bitter old lady!

906
00:55:37,170 --> 00:55:40,080
I think she's just sad
because her husband left her.

907
00:55:42,430 --> 00:55:43,569
Is that what she told you?

908
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,566
You finally got a
boyfriend, Sammy girl?

909
00:55:46,590 --> 00:55:47,752
[crowd giggling]

910
00:55:50,200 --> 00:55:52,742
What's up with
the silly hat, dude?

911
00:55:52,880 --> 00:55:53,386
[sighs]

912
00:55:53,470 --> 00:55:54,620
Shut up, McDonough.

913
00:55:56,540 --> 00:55:58,035
Hey, dude, I'm talking to you.

914
00:55:58,620 --> 00:56:00,518
It's not a hat, it's a topi.

915
00:56:02,680 --> 00:56:03,635
A toe cheese?

916
00:56:03,660 --> 00:56:04,948
[crowd giggling]

917
00:56:05,830 --> 00:56:08,303
Check out the little
dude's toe cheese.

918
00:56:08,860 --> 00:56:10,148
[laughing]

919
00:56:11,870 --> 00:56:12,836
Where you going?

920
00:56:13,900 --> 00:56:15,326
You got a building to blow up?

921
00:56:16,500 --> 00:56:18,927
I asked you a
question, rag head.

922
00:56:19,050 --> 00:56:20,971
Hey leave him
alone. He's just a kid.

923
00:56:21,070 --> 00:56:23,346
It's okay, Sam. I know what
to do with bullies like him.

924
00:56:23,370 --> 00:56:26,015
[crowd booing]

925
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:30,760
And I know what to do
with dirty little Arabs like you.

926
00:56:32,040 --> 00:56:32,903
[chuckles]

927
00:56:33,180 --> 00:56:34,112
What's so funny?

928
00:56:34,770 --> 00:56:37,185
I'm not Arab, I'm Pakistani.

929
00:56:37,760 --> 00:56:39,276
Huh! And there's a difference.

930
00:56:39,300 --> 00:56:40,176
[chuckles]

931
00:56:40,200 --> 00:56:43,294
You don't know the difference
between Arab and Pakistani?

932
00:56:44,500 --> 00:56:44,949
[slaps]

933
00:56:46,090 --> 00:56:47,930
Stop it! Get off of him!

934
00:56:48,350 --> 00:56:50,856
Omar, please just stop!

935
00:56:50,880 --> 00:56:57,746
[somber music]

936
00:56:57,770 --> 00:56:58,932
Yeah!

937
00:57:00,470 --> 00:57:17,496
[music]

938
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:18,130
All right.

939
00:57:19,300 --> 00:57:20,381
Where were you two?

940
00:57:20,680 --> 00:57:22,946
What happened, is that blood?

941
00:57:23,100 --> 00:57:24,630
We were just at the
park. And all of a sudden--

942
00:57:24,650 --> 00:57:25,156
Sam!

943
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:25,878
What?

944
00:57:25,920 --> 00:57:27,316
How could you let this happen?

945
00:57:27,340 --> 00:57:29,186
Well, it's not like I
really had a choice.

946
00:57:29,210 --> 00:57:31,946
Well, you took him to the park,
you were responsible for him.

947
00:57:31,970 --> 00:57:33,666
Yeah. And you took
Uncle Mike to the building.

948
00:57:33,690 --> 00:57:35,396
Does that mean you're
responsible for killing him?

949
00:57:35,420 --> 00:57:37,156
- Samantha Jean McLeod!
- What?

950
00:57:37,180 --> 00:57:38,426
Apologize to her.

951
00:57:38,450 --> 00:57:38,853
No.

952
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:41,266
Yes. You apologize
to her right now.

953
00:57:41,290 --> 00:57:41,624
No!

954
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:44,090
Look, ever since it
happened, all she ever does

955
00:57:44,110 --> 00:57:46,956
is look at me with those
angry eyes like it was my fault.

956
00:57:46,980 --> 00:57:49,166
So if you want to blame
me for her blackened heart

957
00:57:49,190 --> 00:57:50,906
and for getting Omar
beat up, then fine.

958
00:57:50,930 --> 00:57:52,747
Fine. Just blame me for everything.

959
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:56,227
[door closes]

960
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:07,606
You, okay?

961
00:58:09,060 --> 00:58:12,027
I don't think it was such a
good idea to bully the boys.

962
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:16,869
Let's get you cleaned up.

963
00:58:17,320 --> 00:58:19,965
[water trickling]

964
00:58:21,340 --> 00:58:23,295
I'm allowed to touch you
when you're bleeding?

965
00:58:25,300 --> 00:58:25,760
No.

966
00:58:27,840 --> 00:58:29,680
Now here, take this and--

967
00:58:33,110 --> 00:58:34,628
What are you going
to do with that?

968
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:47,992
Who is Uncle Mike?

969
00:58:53,500 --> 00:58:55,064
Michael was my husband.

970
00:58:59,320 --> 00:59:00,884
And you told me
that he left you.

971
00:59:02,830 --> 00:59:03,451
He did.

972
00:59:05,260 --> 00:59:07,698
April 19th, 1995.

973
00:59:09,090 --> 00:59:11,011
He was working in
the federal building.

974
00:59:11,620 --> 00:59:12,828
Oklahoma City

975
00:59:20,330 --> 00:59:22,078
I dropped him off that morning.

976
00:59:24,820 --> 00:59:26,752
Handed him his lunchbox.

977
00:59:27,790 --> 00:59:29,757
And told him I'd pick
him up after work.

978
00:59:31,270 --> 00:59:34,479
I was running late for some
stupid aerobics class and

979
00:59:36,640 --> 00:59:38,296
I forgot to give him a kiss.

980
00:59:44,910 --> 00:59:46,976
It's interesting that some of
the most important moments

981
00:59:47,000 --> 00:59:49,346
in your life happen when
you're not even looking.

982
00:59:53,890 --> 00:59:55,063
I'm really sorry.

983
00:59:58,290 --> 00:59:58,934
Me, too.

984
01:00:03,110 --> 01:00:04,546
You missed a
spot there tough guy.

985
01:00:04,570 --> 01:00:05,099
Oh.

986
01:00:18,210 --> 01:00:19,061
[knocking on door]

987
01:00:19,140 --> 01:00:20,118
Are you okay?

988
01:00:20,950 --> 01:00:22,514
Is the couch comfortable?

989
01:00:24,150 --> 01:00:25,772
Yes, sir. Thank you.

990
01:00:26,870 --> 01:00:27,882
Goodnight, Omar.

991
01:00:30,860 --> 01:00:31,907
Excuse me.

992
01:00:36,020 --> 01:00:37,872
You can talk to God, right?

993
01:00:42,070 --> 01:00:43,864
We all can talk to God.

994
01:00:45,620 --> 01:00:46,966
But you're a holy man.

995
01:00:47,210 --> 01:00:49,878
You've a special, direct
connection with him.

996
01:00:53,660 --> 01:00:55,098
That connection
hasn't

997
01:00:55,590 --> 01:00:58,212
exactly been
working so well lately.

998
01:00:58,280 --> 01:00:58,729
But--

999
01:01:04,290 --> 01:01:06,682
Why does God let
bad things happen?

1000
01:01:09,450 --> 01:01:10,359
[sighs]

1001
01:01:17,660 --> 01:01:18,695
Well,

1002
01:01:22,340 --> 01:01:24,824
some people think that

1003
01:01:25,830 --> 01:01:27,590
God created the Earth and

1004
01:01:28,970 --> 01:01:32,144
everything that happens
after that is just chance.

1005
01:01:34,180 --> 01:01:35,595
Others would say that

1006
01:01:35,690 --> 01:01:38,703
things happen because
of man's free will.

1007
01:01:39,180 --> 01:01:44,091
Sometimes we make good choices,
and sometimes we make bad choices.

1008
01:01:45,830 --> 01:01:46,359
But--

1009
01:01:48,510 --> 01:01:50,396
I think there's
some mystery to it.

1010
01:01:52,330 --> 01:01:53,273
Because there's

1011
01:01:55,240 --> 01:01:57,529
some things that
happen in this world that

1012
01:01:57,790 --> 01:01:58,687
we just can't

1013
01:01:59,430 --> 01:02:00,914
fully understand.

1014
01:02:02,960 --> 01:02:05,053
Like what happened
to Montine's husband.

1015
01:02:06,140 --> 01:02:06,819
Yeah.

1016
01:02:08,020 --> 01:02:09,996
<i>Like what happened
to Montine's husband.</i>

1017
01:02:10,020 --> 01:02:47,106
[somber music]

1018
01:02:47,130 --> 01:02:48,648
Allahu Akbar.

1019
01:02:48,790 --> 01:03:00,296
[music]

1020
01:03:00,320 --> 01:03:01,723
Allahu Akbar.

1021
01:03:01,920 --> 01:03:05,060
[music]

1022
01:03:05,180 --> 01:03:06,572
Allahu Akbar.

1023
01:03:08,710 --> 01:03:09,262
Hey.

1024
01:03:12,410 --> 01:03:13,698
- Let me help you.
- I got it.

1025
01:03:19,220 --> 01:03:19,784
[sighs]

1026
01:03:20,020 --> 01:03:20,963
Hey, aunt Montine.

1027
01:03:24,380 --> 01:03:26,370
I'm sorry about what I
said to you last night.

1028
01:03:28,040 --> 01:03:32,008
I think I can find space in my
blackened heart to forgive you.

1029
01:03:33,500 --> 01:03:34,489
Okay, cool.

1030
01:03:36,540 --> 01:03:39,174
Well, I'm not really into
the whole goodbye thing.

1031
01:03:39,880 --> 01:03:40,800
It's no problem.

1032
01:03:41,650 --> 01:03:42,179
Okay.

1033
01:03:44,560 --> 01:03:46,044
Take good care of your dad.

1034
01:03:47,170 --> 01:03:48,056
[scoffs]
Yeah.

1035
01:03:48,120 --> 01:03:49,075
Somebody has to.

1036
01:04:01,140 --> 01:04:02,302
She hates me.

1037
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:04,592
Now, I'll tell you a secret.

1038
01:04:05,170 --> 01:04:07,769
All 15-year-old girls
hate their fathers.

1039
01:04:11,660 --> 01:04:14,662
All big sisters can't
stand their baby brothers.

1040
01:04:17,840 --> 01:04:19,071
I'll be back on Sunday.

1041
01:04:25,230 --> 01:04:27,714
Hey, I'm sorry again
about those creeps.

1042
01:04:27,760 --> 01:04:30,386
It's okay. It's not
really your fault.

1043
01:04:30,410 --> 01:04:32,032
[car engine revving]

1044
01:04:33,090 --> 01:04:37,288
You know, if you tell Aunt Montine about
the cigarettes, I'm gonna kick your ass.

1045
01:04:43,830 --> 01:05:58,246
[music]

1046
01:05:58,270 --> 01:05:58,799
[door opens]

1047
01:06:02,360 --> 01:06:03,073
[door opens]

1048
01:06:03,080 --> 01:06:04,506
